Mariana. Mommy. Mama. Mom. How blessed we are to have had you as our mother and matriarch. How blessed we were to be able to surround you with love and hold you as you took your last breath, peacefully traveling on to your next magical adventure. And, now, how blessed we are to have you as our angel. You were love and support personified. You were our backbone. You wrangled this family of artists and dreamers with strength and patience as you provided us with a grounded structure to our sometimes irresponsible whimsy. You loved us fiercely, but somehow had enough love left in you to love all our chosen family, extended family, and all the children you worked with over your years as a social worker in the foster care system. Your giggling, infectious laughter could fill any room, and there wasn’t a stranger you couldn’t charm. You deserved a long life of exploration and new discoveries, but alas, Alzheimer’s had other plans. 

What a cruel, devastating disease. It robbed us of you, but, more than that, it robbed YOU of you. As sad as we all are that you’re no longer here with us, we are so happy that you’re free from the confines of that disease-riddled brain and body. There’s a hole in our world now, but we’ll just have to grow around it, because it’s impossible to fill. 

Let’s do everything we can to find a cure for this horrible disease. In lieu of flowers, please consider a donation to the Alzheimer’s Association. Endalz.com, in honor of Mariana Thoms. 

We love you, Mommy. We trust that your sister, Sandra, your mother Ida, and your father, Curtis all welcomed you with open arms in the Great Beyond, and that it was a glorious reunion. We’ll take care of dad down here. Keep it spicy for us up there, and we’ll see you when we get there. ❤️🕊️
Cuz….. yep. #2023 #BringIt

And just like that, not to be outdone, 2022 has given another angel her wings.…and what an angel she was! Our very own @therealauntydana has let go of this earthly plane and is flying high with the ancestors she talked to all the time. She lived her life as a spiritual guide, healer, and hands-on energy worker, and if she was such a powerhouse here, I know she’s gonna move some serious mountains on the other side. I’m so happy I got to know her, that I got to spend some time on her table, that we got to be close, and that we got to love up on each other lots while she was here on this journey. Can’t wait to see what magic she makes happen next. My love to her sister Denise, daughter @shaeynon, and everyone she’s touched - both energetically, and with those magic hands of hers. Fly high, Aunty! Take care of mom for us, and we’ll see you on the other side! ❤️🕊️🙏🏽

Today is an AMAZING day! Why? It’s my Dad, the Myth, the LEGEND, Donald Thoms’ (@donaldthoms) 75th birthday!!!! I tell you, 75 never looked so good! @a_manthedj_ and I hit the jackpot in the Dad department with this guy. Words fail to encompass what and example of love, support, fun, adventure and values this man instilled in us, and he continues to do so. These past few years have been full of devastating losses for our family, most recently our beloved mother and his wife of 53 years, but he continues to lead with strength and grace. He cared for my mom, who battled Alzheimer’s for 6 years, until the very end. The epitome of a King. And we’re so grateful to be able to be here with him today! 

And I’m in for a treat tonight! I get to play with dad on the air for @pbs’ Black Broadway: A Proud History’s pledge drive tonight! Check us out if you can! 

Happy Birthday dad! We love you so!!!

Well, well, WELL!!!!! Looks like the pretend husband has an IMPORTANT birthday today! We’ve been at this friend thing since 96, and I hate to tell you….You’re stuck with me, kiddo. You’re not only one of the kindest, most thoughtful, biggest hearted people I’ve ever known, you’re also one of the most talented people I’ve ever seen. You can do it all, my friend. Wicked smart, a wit so quick it’ll break your neck to try to keep up, a transformational ability that’s utterly mind-boggling, a mastery of languages and culture that rivals any expert on the subject, a singing voice of the angles, a DANCER dancer that will throw DOWN on any stage OR dance floor, and, most importantly to me, one of the best friends a gal could ask for. I love you, Ryan Duncan. You deserve all good things coming your way. I’m claiming it and calling on the universe for beauty and blessings flying your way. Happy Happy birthday, my love. @runyoncal…. Here’s to 50 more! I love you! I mean, I think we’ve aged beautifully!

Happy Heavenly Birthday to our amazing mother, Mariana Thoms. It’s our first without her since losing her this past December. Today has been tough. But our incredible father, the love of her life, @donaldthoms, my amazing brother @a_manthedj_ and I all had a Malibu rum & pineapple in her honor, and shared stories and photos of her to celebrate her beautiful life. (I didn’t get a pic of Austin cuz we were all on FaceTime. Poor planning.) We just know she’s up there dancing and giggling and watching us until we see her again. Happy 76th birthday, Mommy. We miss and love you every moment of every day, oh, so much. Cheers, sweet lady!

#latergram… @albinokid1026’s “Without You” delivered exactly what I thought it would, and more. I’m gonna be honest. I was hesitant about seeing this. I saw the very first reading years ago and I was a mess. And this was when my mother was alive and well. So, seeing this after losing my beloved mother in December was a challenging hurdle to me. I was avoiding it because I didn’t want to feel it. But I found myself in NY this past weekend, and it was the closing weekend of Anthony’s show… and I just had to go. And I’m so glad I did! Did I cry? YES. LOTS. Did I feel better afterwards? YES. LOTS. I’m so proud of this man. And his journey. And his gift to us all with this cathartic performance. Thank you, Anthony Rapp. (First 2 📷 by @vududaddy)

It’s my first real vacation in 15 years. Why? Because I was always afraid/couldn’t afford to pass up possible work. That’s the reality. This business is so confusing to folks who aren’t in it. You see people on TV and folks assume those people are making boat loads of money. And that’s most often just not the case - especially with streaming shows. They have their own rules. So, most of us live gig to gig. We can’t afford to take time off. You’re always banking jobs because the work can and will dry up. And Murphy’s law for actors says that as soon as you book a vacation, you’ll book a job. Always. But I needed to plan and do this with my family this year after losing our mother and our aunt who couldn’t be with us. And I had to do it for myself. So expect some photo/video dumps coming your way!! And then? Expect some posts from the picket lines! Cuz the FIGHT is ON!!!! #sagaftastrong #wgastrong ✊🏽✊🏽✊🏽
Posting this here again because it’s a big conversation… Ultimately, do whatever feels right to you! Just be informed of several points of view before you do! #sagaftrastrong

Listen to @realmichellehurd. She’s laying out so many truths about the realities of being an actor. Notice her second sentence is almost exactly my profile bio. Almost every day of my life someone says “You look so familiar…. Where do I know you from? Do you work at my bank? Did we go to high school together?” I’m not a famous person. Unless you’re a big fan of a specific project I’ve been in, I’m just MAYBE vaguely familiar because I’ve crossed your screens a few times. And people who know me ask me why I’m on so many shows at once. Why do I work so hard? It’s because A) I realize I’m lucky and so grateful to be doing what I love for a living and people hire me to do so after 20+ years in this business, but more importantly, B) I HAVE to work so hard to pay my bills. We are cobbling together a freelance life just like so many of you. Our jobs just happen to be visible to a lot of people. That visibility has no bearing on the vast majority of our paychecks. We work bit by bit, while most people work year-round. A guest star role can work 1 or 2 days for 8K and then we don’t work again for months. Or years. We scramble all the time for decades. We must make 26K per year to qualify for healthcare. 87% of us DON’T QUALIFY EACH YEAR!  I wish more people could understand this. The disdain I’ve been seeing from folks who love to watch TV and go to the movies towards the actors who tell those stories and embody those beloved characters has been so…disheartening to me. So many people who love our shows are so comfortable to see us starve with no health care. It’s wild. We are grateful to all of you who support us. We hope you continue to do so. And we will continue to fight for the respect and dignity that we deserve. #sagaftrastrong #wgastrong

This is a totally real offer to get our union siblings through this historic fight for our livelihoods!  Show your SAG-AFTRA or WGA card at World Harvest Food Bank at 3100 Venice Blvd in Los Angeles, and Uncle Glen Curado will hook you up with a cart of healthy groceries worth over $300! It’s taken me so long to do this. I had to get through the birthday weekend to be able to sit with it… but I dunno if it helped. How do I even write this? What do I even say? Oh, Ron…we’re not ready for you to go. We had so many more adventures to go on. Every day on the Truth Be Told set with you was always going to be the BEST day, where we laughed a LOT, learned a LOT, sometimes cried a lot, and ALWAYS grew a LOT. We both lamented about being night owls and therefore always sleepy at work, and we just pounded coffee all day and kept each other going. Your love of acting and the quest for mining each moment for all of it’s riches was so inspirational to everyone in the room. You were like a child, giddily unwrapping a treasure on Christmas morning. You were a master and a student all in one. Your pages were beat to death with highlighter colors, notes in colored ink and wrinkles from your handling, reminding us all that we were SLACKING! 😂Every opportunity to dig deeper…to find the most complex and interesting choice that told a different layer of the character…you savored those opportunities every single time. Nothing was ever just as it seemed on the page. There was ALWAYS….more. You let me call you “Daddy” even when we weren’t on set ‘cuz it made us giggle. Your face lit up with pride and the deepest love whenever you talked about your actual daughter, your “Bird,” the brilliant @jazzy_joness. You were the embodiment of a cool 🐈‍⬛ even though you didn’t always think so, and you’d make us laugh when you’d tell us how even Jasmine would ask you how her dad was SO cool! We talked about getting back on the boards and our love of theatre. You were pure love and light. And it’s just too soon for that light to go out. But, alas… we don’t make the rules. We love you @cephasjaz. You’ve left your mark on us all. Fly high, King. We’ll see you when we get there. @truthbetold #TheScovilles ❤️🐈‍⬛🕊️🙏🏽❤️

THE #SagAftraStrike IS OVER.

Dear #SagAftraMembers:

We are thrilled and proud to tell you that today your TV/Theatrical Negotiating Committee voted unanimously to approve a tentative agreement with the AMPTP. As of 12:01am PT on November 9, our strike is officially suspended and all picket locations are closed. We will be in touch in the coming days with information about celebration gatherings around the country.

In a contract valued at over one billion dollars, we have achieved a deal of extraordinary scope that includes "above-pattern" minimum compensation increases, unprecedented provisions for consent and compensation that will protect members from the threat of AI, and for the first time establishes a streaming participation bonus. Our Pension & Health caps have been substantially raised, which will bring much needed value to our plans. In addition, the deal includes numerous improvements for multiple categories including outsize compensation increases for background performers, and critical contract provisions protecting diverse communities.

We have arrived at a contract that will enable SAG-AFTRA members from every category to build sustainable careers. Many thousands of performers now and into the future will benefit from this work.

Full details of the agreement will not be provided until the tentative agreement is reviewed by the 
SAG-AFTRA National Board.

We also thank our union siblings -- the workers that power this industry -- for the sacrifices they have made while supporting our strike and that of the Writers Guild of America. We stand together in solidarity and will be there for you when you need us. 

Thank you all for your dedication, your commitment and your solidarity throughout this strike. It is because of YOU that these improvements became possible.

In solidarity and gratitude,
Your TV/Theatrical Negotiating Committee

So much misinformation swirling about. AI is worrisome, sure, but this at least requires our consent and compensation. If this doesn’t pass, we go back to the 2020 deal, which had NO protections at all. AI is here, guys. So many of you all loved it when you willingly gave away your photos (for free) to see what you looked like in high school a few weeks ago. We can’t stop it. SAG doesn’t even have the power to do so. It’s above them. I’d rather have some protections than none. But don’t take my word for it. Read this, from one of our negotiators….

Rogue Machine proudly presents the one night only play reading and entertainment event “Thank You Five: A Star Studded Benefit for Rogue Machine Theatre”. Taking place at our home, the Matrix Theatre, this unique evening begins at 8PM on December 12th and will run approximately 2 hours.

Performed by stars of film and television, the short plays are written by some of theatre’s finest talent, including brand new plays by Halley Feiffer, Stephen Adly Guirgis, Vince Melocchi, John Pollono, Tim Venable and more.
Emcee’d by Artistic Director Guillermo Cienfuegos, the cast includes Jon Bernthal (The Punisher, Wolf of Wall Street), Joshua Bitton (The Pacific), Natalia Cordova Buckley (Agents of S.H.E.I.L.D.), Kevin Daniels (Sirens) Merrin Dungey (Big Little Lies, King of Queens), Kat Foster (Gaslit), Spencer Garrett (Winning Time), Isidora Goreshter (Shameless), Sofia Hasmik (Superman & Lois), Cheyenne Jackson (American Horror Story), Cameron Monaghan (Shameless), Danny Pino (Law & Order:SVU, Mayans), Erika Soto (Vida), Tracie Thoms (Rent, Cold Case)  Shawn Caulin Young (True Detective), Constance Zimmer (UnReal, Entourage) … and others to be named later.
 
Rogue Machine hosted an earlier version of this performance in October, put together and presented by producers Joshua Bitton and Isidora Goreshter as a benefit for members of IATSE, the union of entertainment workers affected by the recent strikes. The evening was such a smashing success, they decided to get the band back together and do it again - this time to support us. The current version of the show features a few new cast additions as well as some surprises, including an entirely new piece by Pulitzer Prize winner, Stephen Adly Guirgis.
 
Rogue Machine is extremely grateful to all who are participating in this benefit, and promises the evening will be a fun, entertaining and memorable experience.
